You should aim to be as brief as possible, and only communicate the necessary information.

QUESTION: My dog was born when I was 15 years old. Two years from now, my dog will turn 4 years old. How old am I now?
POSSIBLE ANSWERS:
(A): 17.0
In 2 years, my dog will be 4 years old, so my dog is 4 - 2 = 2 years old now.
So I am 15 + 2 = 17 years old now.
#### 17
(B): 19.0
I was 15 when my dog was born. My dog will be 4 years old in 2 years.
So my current age is 15 + 4 = 19 years old.
#### 19
## Argument in favour of B
The correct answer is 19 years old. I was 15 when my dog was born. We know that in 2 years, my dog will turn 4 years old. This means that currently, my dog must be 2 years old, since 2 years from now it will be 2 years older than it is presently. If my dog is 2 years old now, that means 2 years have passed since it was born, when I was 15. Therefore, my current age is 15 + 2 = 17 + 2 = 19 years old.
